\f1\b Today is the anniversary of the death of Louis Pasteur
\f2\b0  (1822-1895), {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_people"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 French}} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biologist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 biologist}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microbiologist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 microbiologist}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 chemist}} renowned for his discoveries of the principles of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccination"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 vaccination}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fermentation"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 microbial fermentation}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pasteurization"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 pasteurization}}. He is remembered for his remarkable breakthroughs in the causes and prevention of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diseases"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 diseases}}, and his discoveries have saved many lives ever since. He reduced mortality from {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Puerperal_fever"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 puerperal fever}}, and created the first vaccines for {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rabies"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 rabies}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anthrax"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 anthrax}}.\cb1 \
\cb3 His medical discoveries provided direct support for the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germ_theory_of_disease"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 germ theory of disease}} and its application in clinical medicine. He is best known to the general public for his invention of the technique of treating {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milk"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 milk}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wine"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 wine}} to stop bacterial contamination, a process now called {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pasteurization"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 pasteurization}}. \
Today, he is often regarded as one of the fathers of germ theory.
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super [8]
\fs28 \cf2 \nosupersub  Pasteur made significant \cf4 discoveries\cf2  in chemistry, most notably on the molecular basis for the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asymmetry"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 asymmetry}} of certain {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crystals"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 crystals}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Racemization"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 racemization}}. Early in his career, his investigation of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tartaric_acid"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 tartaric acid}} resulted in the first resolution of what is now called {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chirality_(chemistry)"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 optical isomers}}. His work led the way to the current understanding of a fundamental principle in the structure of organic compounds.\cb1 \
